well_activity_remarks_html:
WELL_NAME API12 WAR_START_DT TEXT_REMARK
0 001 608124007500 2012-06-29 06/29/2012: Pick up and run 36" casing with Jet in assembly; jet in 36" to 6;251' (332' BML). 06/30/2012: POOH w/ jet in assy. TIH w/ 26" drlg assy and drill ahead f/ 6;251' to 6529'.
1 001 608124007500 2012-07-01 07/01/2012: Drilled 26" hole section to TD from 6;251' to 8;303'. NOTE: Top of Salt 6;749'. 07/02/2012: Circulated bottoms up with 12.5 ppg SSM; Made short trip f/ 8;303' to 6;190'; Hole was slick with no fill on bottom. POOH w/ 26" drilling assembly and rig up 22" casing equipment. 07/03/2012: R/U and RIH w/ 22" csg to 2;357'. 07/04/2012: RIH w/ 22" csg to 8;263'. Circulate with 12.5 ppg WBM. Cement with 8320 cu/ft Class H cement followed by 1689 cu/ft Class H cement. Total of 10;009 cu/ft cement pumped. Note: Lost 100% returns after mixing 365 bbl of lead cement. 07/05/2012: POOH with 72# landing string; lay out FMC running tool; POOH with 5" stinger. Slip and Cut drill line; change out swivel packing on top drive. Sub Sea performing stump test. 07/06/2012: Pick up 16 stds of 6 5/8" 40# drill pipe; drift to 4.125"; rack same in derrick. Stump test BOPs Rig up riser equipment; Identify leak on BOP's. RD equipment on BOP; prepare to split and repair same. 07/07/2012: Disassemble BOP accumulator bottles; hoses; valves and related equipment preparing to split BOP's for repair.
2 001 608124007500 2012-07-08 07/08/2012: Start rig up of BOP support frame. The frame sent to the rig did not cover the entire width of the BOP elevator which Ensco Engineers deemed insufficient to support the weight for repairs . General maintenance while waiting on material for BOP lift frame. 07/09/2012: PM's and housekeeping; painting projects. Welders start fabrication of BOP lift frame; adding liquid additives to R&D unit for SBM. Note: ROV perform well head inspection @ 07:05 hrs. No oil bubbles observed @ sea floor. Observed surface expression on port side of rig @ 11:00 hrs and increase to port; aft and starboard by 15:00 hr before dissipating. 07/10/2012: PM's and housekeeping. Fabricate beams and split rams for inspection. Note: ROV dove @ 07:26 hrs. to do well head inspection and bottom survey; back on deck 11:30 bulls-eye reading was 1/2 degree/heading 270°. No oil bubbles observed @ sea floor. Observed surface expressions @ 18:00 hrs. on stbd side of rig. 07/11/2012: Inspect BOP's and reassemble same; PM's and housekeeping. 07/12/2012: Continue bolting up and testing BOPs. GE/Hydril inspecting BOP's. 07/13/2012: Open top set of bonnet doors on all three sets of double ram preventers. Obtain flange tolerances. Re-torque flange bolts between middle and lower double ram preventers. Break; separate and inspect flanges between lower double ram and wellhead connector. 07/14/2012: Continue with BOP stack inspection and reassembly. Shell test BOP stack. Re torque flange bolts. Check flange tolerances on flange between middle and lower ram doubles. Note: ROV dove @ 06:15; on deck @ 09:40. Perform wellhead and on bottom survey.. Bulls-eye eye reading 1/2 degree @ 270 degree heading. No bubbles observed approximately 250 feet in all directions from WR 51 #1 wellhead. No surface expressions sighted.
3 001 608124007500 2012-07-15 07/15/2012: Re-torque flange between middle and lower double rams Open LPR bonnets and check flange tolerance between middle and lower double rams. Connect control lines on MPR and LPR. Install and connect accumulator bottle racks on BOP. Clean and inspect riser seal. 07/16/2012: Connect accumulator lines and control lines on BOP. Repair lower outer choke fail safe valve operator. Pre- charge BOP accumulator bottle banks to 7;600 psi. 07/17/2012: Nitrogen pre-charge on accumulator bottles on BOP stack. Prep and stack LMRP on BOP. Perform full function on both pods; both SEMs from TPR and DCP. 07/18/2012: Continue with nitrogen pre-charge on BOP accumulator bottles. Prepare and install funnel on BOP. Assist subsea to install and torque operator on LOC of 1;070 ft/lbs. Latch BOP to test stump; prepare for BOP test. Greased LOC. Test LOC operator to 3;000 psi for 5 min.. (ok). Finished with nitrogen pre- charge on BOP accumulator bottles to 7;600 psi. Pressure up on BOP accumulators. Repair leaks on accumulator line connections. Found one accumulator bottle with a ruptured bladder. Replace bladder and charge same with nitrogen to 7;600 psi. Pressure test UPR ( on 6-5/8" ) Upper outer choke fail safe; outer bleed valve; kill test valve and choke test valve to 250 psi low for 5 min.. and 15;000 psi high for 15 min. utilizing ITP Sure-Tec. Hydraulic tech and mechanic performed PM's on TDS. Hydraulic tech and mechanic changed hydraulic flow control valve on lower jaw of ST-120. RU 1000 T bales and elevators. PU riser running tool and RU riser torque tools and function same. Rolled SBM in SLM # 14 and #15 for 30 min. each. Note: BSEE inspectors; Cedric Bernard and Jeramie Liner; arrived on rig at 09:49 hrs on 7/18/12 to witness BOP Stump testing. They will remain on rig throughout stump testing. 07/19/2012: BOP stump pressure test # 4 - # 13 07/20/2012: Complete stump pressure test of BOP's. Conduct auto shear/ deadman function. Conduct EDS and ROV intervention. Re- test LMRP connector. Initiated 12 hour pod soak. 07/21/2012: Soak test pods. Prepare BOP for run. Bridge performed inclination test. Skid BOP to well center. MU boost jt. and riser jt. # 1 to BOP. Lower into splash zone. Run riser jt. # 2- # 5. Test conduit and choke and kill lines. Run riser jt.# 6.
4 001 608124007500 2012-07-22 07/22/2012: Ran BOP on marine riser. PT C/K and rigid conduit @ jt. 41. 74 of 78 total jts. run. 7/23/2012: Run bops and riser; land and latch same; attempt to function Auto shear with no success. Discuss options with Ensco office; R/u to unlatch bops and pull same to trouble shoot and repair same. Test 22" casing and BSR to 250 psi low - 5 min.. and 4;800 psi high - 30 min. 07/24/2012: Trouble shoot auto shear/dead man function; rig up to pull BOP; lay out jewelry. Unlatch and pull BOP. 07/25/2012: Pull BOP's to surface. Skid to stow position. Troubleshooting Auto Shear function. 07/26/2012: Continue trouble shooting Auto Shear circuit; fabricating bracket to invert arm/disarm valve 180° and re-routing plumbing for same; troubleshooting analog board from yellow pod. 07/27/2012: Replace the VMIVME board and analog interface board; this corrected the issue with manifold regulator pilot read back. Completed installation of piping on Auto shear assembly. Service and check riser running equipment. Perform PMs on drilling equipment. 07/28/2012: Function test Auto Shear circuit. Remove and investigate failure of arm/disarm valve; no damage found; re-assemble and re-install for further testing.
5 001 608124007500 2012-07-29 07/29/2012: Test Auto Shear circuit; 50% of auto shear functions failed. Change 3 ruptured bladders in BOP acc. bottles. 07/30/2012: Changed out 3 BOP accumulator bladders and pre-charge same; remove and disassemble POCV f/ BOP; reassemble and test same 3000 psi; good test. Disassemble; inspect; reassemble 2 new POCV; test 1st new POCV for auto shear circuit to 3000 psi; good test. 07/31/2012: Sub Sea function and pressure test 2 Hyvair POCV's; Assist TIC plumbing lines to install equipment in auto shear circuit. Sub Sea repair leaks on test hose and fittings; PM's and rig maintenance. Note:Ensco SubSea Rep Brian Bailey & 2 new Gilmore POCV's arrived on board @ 17:16hrs. Note: Received letter of approval for "safe welding and burning area from Bryan A. Domangue with BSEE Houma District 08/01/2012: Complete 50 cycle function and pressure test of 2 new Gilmore POCV's for auto shear arm/disarm circuit; install POCV's; filter; 1 quart accumulator bottle and gauges in auto shear circuit. PM's; general maintenance and paint projects around rig. 08/02/2012: Function test Auto Shear circuit; soak test pods. Prepare riser running equipment. Wait on BOP parts from Hydril and TIC in Houston. PM's and general maintenance. 08/03/2012: Soak test both pods; install new hydrate seal; Start securing rig; Receive BOP parts; assemble and install same. Storm Evac. time 67 hrs. POB 106. Non-Essential 62. 08/04/2012: Waiting on weather. Monitor tropical storm Ernesto. Continue working on PM's. Continue securing rig. General housekeeping around rig. Training new employees on drilling equipment.
6 001 608124007500 2012-08-05 08/05/2012: Monitor TS Ernesto; Continue with PM's and Housekeeping. Lower BOP to water; h/u test lines on rig floor and test auxiliary lines. Set BOP on cart with 5k hyd pressure on pods and monitor for leaks. Storm evacuation time 64 hrs. POB 105; Non- Essential 61. 08/06/2012: WOW; Run 3 jts of riser & noted ground fault; Pull BOP and trouble shoot ground fault on yellow pod. 08/07/2012: Pressure test ERA connector; change ruptured accumulator bladder; deploy BOP's run 13 of 78 jt's. 08/08/2012: Running riser jt #29 jt's to #78. Flush & test Conduit. 08/09/2012: Test C/K and conduit lines. PU TJ and install SALT ring halves. Hook up SDL ring & transfer string wt to SDL. Land & latch BOP. Test BSR / Csg to 250 psi low and 4800 psi high. Prep to install diverter. 08/10/2012: Install diverter. RD riser running tools. Install rotary table; change bails & elevators; RU to run dp. TIH w/ FMC test assembly. Land out and rig up to test BOP's. Test BOP's and related surface equipment per test procedure to 250 psi low and 5000 psi high. NOTE: BSEE representative Mr. Robert Nelson approved the revisions to the BOP auto shear hydraulic circuit on 8-10-12. 08/11/2012: Complete BOP test. Function diverter & pump sea water through same. Function BOP. TOH; R/U W/L & run CBL.
7 001 608124007500 2012-08-12 08/12/2012: Pull Schlumberger CBL 8;100' to 5;948'. RD Schlumberger. PU / MU BHA #3. Shallow test MWD - Failed. POH and LD Telescope. 08/13/2012: TIH tag cmt @ 8132'. Displace with 11.5 ppg SBM. Drill cmt 8;132' to 8;263'; tag formation; drill 10 ft rat hole to 8'313'; perform FIT. Obtain slow pump rates & record CL frictions. 08/14/2012: Drill F/ 8;313' T/ 10;002. Activate Smith Rhino reamer @ 8;277'. Verify it to be open. Drill to 10;002'. Relog well f/ 9;908' to 10;002' due to Schlumberger depth encoder failure. 08/15/2012: Drill 18-1/8" x 21-1/2" hole f/ 10;002 T/ 10;414'. Lost Node 7 on DCP for BOP. Descision was made to displace well head to TD with 14.3 ppg mud . Circulate while weighting up pits to 14.3 ppg. 08/16/2012: Circulate @ 10;414' while weighting up pits to 14.3 ppg. Displace well from TD to wellhead with 14.3 ppg SBM. TOH t/ 5;603'. Perform negative test. Displace riser; kill and boost line with seawater for BOP DCP repairs. 08/17/2012: POH. t/ 540'. Re-dress and re-pin FMC wear sleeve on running tool. TIH t/ 1;569'. Slip & cut drill line. TIH t/ 7;229'. Function BOP and diverter. Circulate out seawater & 14.3 ppg SBM.. TIH t/ 8;888'. Circulate out 14.3 ppg SBM. 08/18/2012: Displace 14.3 ppg SBM @ 8;888'. TIH t/ 10;414'. Displace 14.3 ppg SBM @ 10;414'. Drill 18-1/8" x 21-1/2" hole f/ 10;414' to 11;650'.
8 001 608124007500 2012-08-19 08/19/2012: Drill 18-1/8" x 21-1/2" hole f/ 11;650' to 12;798'. Decision was made to suspend drilling operations to displace well with 13.6 ppg mud and riser with seawater and pull above BOP to repair Node 5 on BOP control. Weight up 3;300 bbls SBM t/ 13.6 ppg. 08/20/2012: Circ. @ 12;797' while waiting up 3;300 bbls. 13.6 ppg SBM. Displace hole ( f/ TD to wellhead) with 13.6 ppg SBM. POH above BOP. Displace choke line with H2O; close BSR and perform negative test. Apply 1100 psi below BSR and close FSV. Displace riser w/H20 08/21/2012: POOH F/ 5;867' to 542'; Re-dress FMC W/B. GE still collecting data. well_activity_remarks_dict.TEXT_REMARK:
06/29/2012:
Pick up and run 36" casing with Jet in assembly; jet in 36" to 6;251' (332' BML).

06/30/2012:
POOH w/ jet in assy. TIH w/ 26" drlg assy and drill ahead f/ 6;251' to 6529'.

07/01/2012:
Drilled 26" hole section to TD from 6;251' to 8;303'. NOTE: Top of Salt 6;749'.

07/02/2012:
Circulated bottoms up with 12.5 ppg SSM; Made short trip f/ 8;303' to 6;190'; Hole was slick with no fill on bottom. POOH w/ 26" drilling assembly and rig up 22" casing equipment.

07/03/2012:
R/U and RIH w/ 22" csg to 2;357'.

07/04/2012:
RIH w/ 22" csg to 8;263'. Circulate with 12.5 ppg WBM. Cement with 8320 cu/ft Class H cement followed by 1689 cu/ft Class H cement.  Total of 10;009 cu/ft cement pumped.
Note: Lost 100% returns after mixing 365 bbl of lead cement.

07/05/2012:
POOH with 72# landing string; lay out FMC running tool; POOH with 5" stinger. Slip and Cut drill line; change out swivel packing on top drive. Sub Sea performing stump test.

07/06/2012:
Pick up 16 stds of 6 5/8" 40# drill pipe; drift to 4.125"; rack same in derrick. Stump test BOPs Rig up riser equipment; Identify leak on BOP's. RD equipment on BOP; prepare to split and repair same.

07/07/2012:
Disassemble BOP accumulator bottles; hoses; valves and related equipment preparing to split BOP's for repair.

07/08/2012:
Start rig up of BOP support frame. The frame sent to the rig did not cover the entire width of the BOP elevator which Ensco Engineers deemed insufficient to support the weight for repairs . General maintenance while waiting on material for BOP lift frame.

07/09/2012:
PM's and housekeeping; painting projects. Welders start fabrication of BOP lift frame; adding liquid additives to R&D unit for SBM.  Note: ROV  perform well head inspection @ 07:05 hrs. No oil bubbles observed @ sea floor. Observed surface expression on port side of rig @ 11:00 hrs and increase to port; aft and starboard by 15:00 hr before dissipating.

07/10/2012:
PM's and housekeeping. Fabricate beams and split rams for inspection. Note: ROV dove @ 07:26 hrs. to do well head inspection and bottom survey; back on deck 11:30 bulls-eye reading was 1/2 degree/heading 270°. No oil bubbles observed @ sea floor. Observed surface expressions @ 18:00 hrs. on stbd side of rig.

07/11/2012:
Inspect BOP's and reassemble same; PM's and housekeeping.

07/12/2012:
Continue bolting up and testing BOPs. GE/Hydril inspecting BOP's.

07/13/2012:
Open top set of bonnet doors on all three sets of double ram preventers. Obtain flange tolerances. Re-torque flange bolts between middle and lower double ram preventers. Break; separate and inspect flanges between lower double ram and wellhead connector.

07/14/2012:
Continue with BOP stack inspection and reassembly. Shell  test BOP stack. Re torque flange bolts. Check flange tolerances on flange between middle and lower ram doubles.
Note: ROV dove @ 06:15; on deck @ 09:40. Perform wellhead and on bottom survey.. Bulls-eye eye reading 1/2 degree @ 270 degree heading. No bubbles observed approximately 250 feet in all directions from WR 51 #1 wellhead. No surface expressions sighted.

07/15/2012:
Re-torque flange between middle and lower double rams Open LPR bonnets and check flange tolerance between middle and lower double rams. Connect control lines on MPR and LPR. Install and connect accumulator bottle racks on BOP. Clean and inspect riser seal.

07/16/2012:
Connect accumulator lines and control lines on BOP. Repair lower outer choke fail safe valve operator. Pre- charge BOP accumulator bottle banks to 7;600 psi.

07/17/2012:
Nitrogen pre-charge on accumulator bottles on BOP stack. Prep and stack LMRP on BOP. Perform full function on both pods; both SEMs from TPR and DCP.

07/18/2012:
Continue with nitrogen pre-charge on BOP accumulator bottles. Prepare and install funnel on BOP. Assist subsea to install and torque operator on LOC of 1;070 ft/lbs. Latch BOP to test stump; prepare for BOP test. Greased LOC. Test LOC operator to 3;000 psi for 5 min.. (ok). Finished with nitrogen pre- charge on BOP accumulator bottles to 7;600 psi. Pressure up on BOP accumulators. Repair leaks on accumulator line connections. Found one accumulator bottle with a ruptured bladder. Replace bladder and charge same with nitrogen to 7;600 psi. Pressure test UPR ( on 6-5/8" ) Upper outer choke fail safe; outer bleed valve; kill test valve and choke test valve to 250 psi low for 5 min.. and 15;000 psi high for 15 min. utilizing ITP Sure-Tec. Hydraulic tech and mechanic performed PM's on TDS. Hydraulic tech and mechanic changed hydraulic flow control valve on lower jaw of ST-120. RU 1000 T bales and elevators. PU riser running tool and RU riser torque tools and function same. Rolled SBM in SLM # 14 and #15 for 30 min. each.

First report of operations for rig commissioning and acceptance testing of the Ensco 8505 BOP and cement unit:

Ensco 8505 rig arrived on location on 5/3/2012 at 16:00 hrs.  General rig maintenance; housekeeping and troubleshooting issues until this weekly activity period.  

5/13/2012 - 
Perform BOP operator pressure tests @ 3;000 psi f/mins.  Tested wellhead connector lock; unlock and secondary unlock. (Good test).  Commence function testing BOPs.  West Engineering performing verification of compatibility BOP documentation.


5/14/2012 -
Continue function testing BOPs on all pods at all stations and sems.

5/15/2012 -
Perform EDS sequence per procedure.  Begin stump testing BOPs from CCU station; blue pod; SEM B blind shear rams (250-15000 psi).

5/16/2012 -
Test blind shear rams; UIK; LIK; UIC; & LIC valves @ 250 & 15000 psi f/10 mins.  Continue stump testing BOPs (250-15000 psi).

5/17/2012 -
Continue stump testing BOPs.  Performed EDS on BOP from drillers panel; 23 seconds.

5/18/2012 -
USCG on board for inspection.  COC issued.  Completed BOP stump testing. Test autoshear; and drift BOP.

5/19/2012 -
Drift BOPs & LMRP with drift tool.  Tested auto-shear circuit as per procedure.  Pre-charging subsea BOP accumulator bottles.

5/20/2012 - 
Continuing pre-charging of accumulator bottles and preparing BOPs for riser run.

5/21/2012 -
Perform rig maintenance; housekeeping and PM's.  Continue to troubleshoot general rig commissioning issues.

5/22/2012 -
Continue pre-charging BOPs.  ROV performed surface function test on BOPs.

5/23/2012 -
Finished pre-charging subsea BOP accumulator bottles.  Perform soak test on blue and yellow pods.  Repair leaks.  Function test BOPs.  Drift stack.  Verify function of riser running equipment.  Preparing for BOP run. 

5/24/2012 -
Prepare and skid BOP to well center.  Connect boost and slick riser joints to BOPs; check bullseye readings on BOP.  Perform inclination test with 200k pulled on BOP.  Troubleshoot inclination indicator on yellow pod.  Perform inclination testing on blue pod; good test.

5/25/2012 -
P/U BOPs from cart; run 2 joints of riser.  Make up test hoses; fill line; test conduit line 5000 psi for 5 minutes; fill and test choke and kill lines to 250/10;000 psi for 5 minutes each; good test.  Complete pressure test on choke and kill lines; good test.  Continue running riser; 6 jts. out of 76 jts. ran.

5/26/2012 -
Continue running riser; 32 jts. out of 77 jts.; checking seals and charging BOPs as needed.

5/27/2012 -
Continue running riser 57 of 77 jts ran.  Rig up and test lines.  Schlumberger test choke and kill lines 250/10k 5 min each with sea water; rig test conduit link 5k 5 minutes.

5/28/2012 -
Continue running riser. Make up 10' riser pup joint and re-test lines. Choke and kill lines 20/10k for 6 min each.  Install SALT ring on telescopic joint.

5/29/2012 - 
Position rig over wellhead; land and latch BOP on CMC; perform 100k over pull to verify latch.  Install diverter and perform 20K over pull to ensure latch.  Attempt to test diverter to 500 psi.  

5/30/2012 - 
Continue testing diverter. Pick up test joint and RIH. Testing BOPE 250/15000 psi 5 min. each

5/31/2012 - 
Continue pressure and function testing BOPE.

6/1/2012 -
Function test blind rams and shear rams with yellow pod. Continue to pressure test BOPE. Performed ROV intervention; ROV function pipe shear rams.  Test cement manifold 250/10k; good test.  Performed accumulator drill on BOP system.

6/2/2012 -
TIH to 5653' with 6-5/8" drill pipe in preparation for EDS test.  Organize rig equipment; general housekeeping.

06/03/2012 -
TIH f/5653' to 5848'.  Performed EDS test.  Position rig 150' off location.  ROV replaced ring gasket on connector.  Closed lower annual and regulated pressure to 1500 psi.  Position rig back over stack.  Land out LMRP onto BOPs with 100k down.  Locked connector in.  100k over pull to verify good latch.  Shear rams did not function during test.  POOH f/5696' to surface.  Transferred riser running equipment to rig floor.

06/04/2012 -
Rig up rig floor to pull riser.  P/U and M/U riser landing jt. Stroked out CMC; lowered inner barrel on TJ; set down 20k; latched and over pulled to confirm proper latch.  Began bleeding off tensioners taking weight with CMC/Block.  Unlatch BIO f/wellhead and verify proper gal count for unlatch function; 18.2 gal.  BOP lift off from wellhead.  Move off location 100'.  ROV set wellhead cap; moved another 400' off location; for a total of 500'.  Proceed to pick up till SDL ring is in latch position on the diverter housing over pulled 40k; latched and secured with locking dogs.  Lower string to salt ring removal position.

Pull BOPs and riser.

Test choke and kill lines to 250 low and 15;000 high.  Remove SALT ring handling tools and secure same.  Latch tensioner ring to telescopic jt. and pull 100k to verify proper latch.  Pressure up on tensioners and CMC.  ROV removed TA cap from wellhead.  Position rig over wellhead.  Land BOP and latch wellhead connector.  Pull test 100K to verify proper latch.  Good.  Transfer riser weight to tensioners.  Connect telescopic joint control lines.  Unlock inner barrel and scope out telescopic jt.

5/18/2012 -

Halliburton displace cement with 230 bbls of 8.6ppg seawater; Lift pressure was 231 psi and with pumps off pressure was 440 psi. Cement in place at 23:40 Hrs. Floats holding.

Note: Saw green dye at well head. PH of returns at well head went from 7.6 to 13.5. 

12/21/2016- POOH and L/D running tool. POOH with 6 5/8" inner string. Change out BHA and TIH to 7146'. Drill cmt/ shoe to 7233'. Displace drill string and 28" casing with 10.5 ppg. Wash down from 7;233' to 7;378'. Drill to 7;472' MD/TVD.

12/22/2016- Drill to 8;537' MD/TVD. Circulate B/U. Displace well with 12.5 ppg SSWBM. POOH. Run 22" to 7975'.

12/23/2016- Continue running 22" casing and land out 22" in the LPH with the shoe at 8;497' MD/TVD. pump 10 bbls of 15.0ppg Un-dyed tuned spacer III; Halliburton pump 120 bbls of 15.0 ppg tuned spacer III; foamed back to 12.0 ppg (First 50 bbls of spacer has 3 gal/bbl of green dye). Halliburton mix and pump Foamed Lead cement Class H +.07% EzFlo ll +1.88 #/sk; KCL +.09 GPS; Zoneseal 2000+.25 GPS; Deep FX-L + 0.13 GPS; DWFS. 1882.9 sacks; Surface volumes: cu/ft surface 1951; barrels surface 347; density surface 16.9 ppg ; Foamed volumes = cu/ft downhole 2473; barrels downhole 441; density downhole 13.8 ppg; Pump rate 4 bbls per min. Halliburton mix and pump Foamed Tail cement; Class H +.07% EzFlo ll +1.88 lb/sk; KCL +.09 GPS; Zoneseal 2000L +.25 GPS; Deep FX-L +.13 GPS calcl2. 1350 sacks; Surface volumes: cu/ft surface 1405; barrels surface 250; density surface 16.9 ppg ; Foamed volumes = cu/ft downhole 1731; barrels downhole 308; density downhole 14.2 ppg; Rate 4 bbls per minute. Halliburton mix and pump Unfoamed Tail cement; Class H + 0.07% E-Z Flo 2 + 1.88 lb/sk KCL + 0.09 gps Zone Seal 2000L + 0.25 gps Deep FX-L + 0.13 gps CaCl2. 1467 sacks. Surface volumes: cu/ft surface 1527; barrels surface 272; density surface 16.9 ppg ; Halliburton displace cement with 245 bbls of 8.6ppg seawater. Lift pressure was 909 psi and with pumps off pressure was 785 psi. Cement in place at 07:40 Hrs. Floats holding.

Note: Saw green dye at well head. Cement back to surface after pumping 110 bbl mix water on foamed tail. PH of returns at well head went from 7.6 to 12.7 and sustained. 
Release from the wellhead and POOH w/ Landing String and inner string. Move rig to safe zone and begin Running BOPs. 

12/24/2016- Continue running riser and BOP.
"},{"   ":121,"WELL_NAME":"  003","API12":608124011300,"WAR_START_DT":"2016-12-25","TEXT_REMARK":"12/25/2016- Land and latch the BOP. Perform ROV intervention test closing Lower blind shear rams. Test well head connector and Lower BSR's to 300 psi low and 4;500 psi for 5 min test on chart. Open lower BSR's. Perform Deadman/Autoshear test. Test 22" casing; cement plug and connector against Upper BSR's to 4;500 psi for 30 min on chart. P/U drilling/test assy and TIH to test BOP.

Note:  APC received verbal approval from Justin Ledet; BSEE Houma District to proceed with previously approved drilling operations.

12/26/2016- Function test BOPs on the Blue POD secondary panel on 6.625'' drill pipe. 

Swap to Yellow POD. Test BOP's against 6.625" .522 wall DP with 8.6 ppg sea water on Yellow POD from Primary panel (Driller Panel). Test Annulars and related valves to 250psi low/ 5;000psi high for 5 min each test. Test VBR's; related valves; surface equipment; TDX auto and manual
IBOP's and kelly hose to 250psi low/ 5;000psi high for 5 min each test. Test 9 of 13 complete.

Note: Test #6 failed due to a leak on the hammer union of the side entry sub. Change seal and re-test as 6A. Close Upper Pipe Rams w/ ROV on Test #7. 18.36 gals @ 21.9 secs to close. Function Diverter on 6.525'' Drill pipe from secondary station @ 06:56 hrs. 34 seconds to close.

Swap to Blue POD and function test upper blind shear rams; function lower blind shear rams; function casing shear rams from secondary panel. (Tool pushers panel).

Swap to Yellow POD and pressure test upper blind shear rams from primary station (Driller panel) Test # 10. Noted good test on low pressure with 300 psi. Attempted to obtain high pressure of 10;500 psi and noted leak of 65 psi/min. Bled down pressure. Function Choke manifold valves pressure back up and noted leak. Test 10 A. Continue to trouble shoot leak. Isolated surface to subsea Tested choke manifold at high pressure only. Choke manifold surface holding pressure. Bled off pressure Line up BOP to test against FMC S.L.T. and UBSR.

Note leak. Decision was made to make up into EDPHOT. Unseat FMC S.L.T. and noted .6 bbl gain in trip tank. Halliburton pump @ 3 BPM to attempt to wash off any possible debris on S .L.T. Shut down pump turn S.L.T. with 1/2 turn and s/off and reset tool in W.H. Release from tool and attempt to Test UBSR against S.L.T. with no success. Decision was made to POOH with S.L.T. and check seals.

Inspect and service FMC spring loaded test plug as per FMC rep.  Rack back same in derrick.  
TIH with 18.125" x 21.5" from 757' to 1;373'. Monitoring well on trip tank; proper displacement noted. Make up EDPHOT assembly as per FMC rep. TIH with EDPHOT assembly and 18.125" x 21.5" drilling BHA from 1;373' to 7;360'. Land out FMC SLT in wellhead at 5;970' (7;360' bit depth).

Attempting to test shear rams. Pressure up against upper shear rams to 11;000 psi; observe bleeding off 80 - 90 psi/min. Close lower shear rams; pressure up to 10;500 psi. Observe pressure bleeding off at 80 - 90 psi/min. Bled pressure to 0 psi. Mix and pump 20 bbls of dyed SW with Halliburton; down kill line and spot in BOPs. Close upper shear rams. ROV dove to monitor for leaks on BOP stack. While pressuring up; green dye was observed coming from connector port at 3;633 psi. Stop Halliburton and bled pressure to 0 psi. Make up into EDPHOT; pull same from wellhead. POOH with EDPHOT assembly from 7;360' to 4;530'. Monitoring well on trip tank; proper well fill noted. Increase wellhead connector locking pressure to 3000 psi. Line up to break circulation down choke line with Halliburton.

12/27/2016- Attempt to test the UBSR/LBSR with no success due to leak at connector. POOH and rack back BHA/ Test Assembly. R/U riser handling eq.; Pull diverter; P/U landing jt. Lock S/J; unlock connector. Lift off BOPs 20'; move vessel 25' to safe zone. Observed hydrate seal on wellhead. ROV remove hydrate seal and inspect gasket.
Pull ring gasket with ROV; bring same to surface. At 17:30 hrs ROV on deck. Move vessel 25'; total 50' off location. ROV going down with 3 ring gaskets ( 2 VGX; 1 resilient). Inspect BOP connector with the ROV and ensure top of wellhead was clean. Move vessel 50' over well center. Land out BOPs with 100K down. Lock wellhead connector; verify with ROV on indicator and proper gallon count (8.7 gallons). Take 50K overpull on yellow pod. Lock ring gasket onto connector. Line up Halliburton; pump down choke line breaking circulation. Close lower blind shear rams; Halliburton pumping at ½ bpm. Test 300/ 2500 psi with sw on chart; good test. Swap to blue pod; perform 50K overpull. Break circulation with Halliburton; close upper blind shear rams. Pressure test to 4;500 psi with seawater on chart; good test.

12/28/2016- Land and lock the BOP. TIH w/ EDPHOT assy. Continue BOP test from Primary station (Driller panel) on yellow pod with 8.6 ppg sea water. Test upper and lower blind shear rams and related valves to 300 psi low/ 10;500psi high for 5 min each test. Function diverter from driller console (primary station); POOH w/ EDPHOT assy. TIH w/ SLB BHA on 6.625" DP. Tag TOC at 8;397'. Displace well with 14.2 SBM. Continue to circulate.

12/29/2016- Drill from 8;397' (TOC) to 8;537' plus 10' of new formation to 8;547'. (Drilled shoe at 8;497'; drilled out of cement @ 8;503'.) Perform FIT to 720 psi surface pressure with 11.2 ppg SBM. EMW 12.84 ppg surface MW + .19 = 13.03 PPG DHMW. Drill ahead to 9;753'. DHMW 11.79 ppg.

12/30/2016- Drilling ahead with Schlumberger 18.125" x 21.5" Drilling Assembly to 12;220'. DHMW 12.09 ppg

12/31/2016- Continue Drilling ahead with Schlumberger 18.125" x 21.5" drilling assembly to 14;506'. Raised mud weight to 12.2ppg SBM. DHMW 12.39 ppg.

Note: Inclusion at 12;262' to 12;268' consisting of calcareous shale.
"},{"   ":122,"WELL_NAME":"  003","API12":608124011300,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-01-01","TEXT_REMARK":"1/1/2017- Circulate hole clean from 14;506'.  Flow check well at shoe; well static. POOH to Rig up and run 18" casing to 3;454'

1/2/2017- Pick up and RIH with 18" casing to 6;344'. TIH with 6.625" (.522 wall dp) inner string to 6;116. Continue RIH with 18" casing on 6.625" .813 wall DP to 14;332'. Slack off from 14;332' to 14;375' and Land out casing in 18" SMLH. Break circulation and circulate bottoms up. No losses observed during circulation.

1/3/2017- Continue Circ BU @ 14;376' with 12.2ppg SBM. No losses observed during circulation. Break circulation and pump a total of 10 bbls of 13.0 ppg Tuned Spacer. Close the Lo-Torque and test lines to 5;000 psi. Good Test; open the Lo-Torque valve. Pump 90 bbls of 13.0 ppg of Tuned Spacer III with surfactants. Mix and Pump 1688 sxs. Class H of cement for 325 bbls ( 1;829.8 ft3.) at 16.4 ppg. with a yield of 1.084 ft3/sk. (Note: pump 10 bbls of cement and inject Protechnics Tracer at 8 MC/Hr into the next 50 bbls at the pump suction.) Pump 15 bbls of 13.0 Tuned SpacerIII with surfactants. Displace the cement with 370 bbls of 12.2 ppg SBM pumped at 8 bpm. Lift pressure 1110 psi; Cement in place at 04:30 hrs. Full Returns experienced during cement job

Note: Shoe - 14;375.30; Float Collar - 14;277.93; 18" TOL Hanger - 8;021

Set & test FMC 18" packoff. Pull up to 13;692' & circ 1.5 tbg vols. TIH w/ 16.5"X 19.5" drlg assy to 5;393'. Test 18" X 22" casing against LBSR's to 2;500psi on circle chart with 12.2 ppg SBM for 30 min on yellow pod from secondary (Tool pusher) panel (Good Test). Function test Upper/Lower BSR's and CSR on yellow pod from secondary ( Tool pusher) panel. Swap to Blue pod. Function test Upper/Lower BSR's and CSR on blue pod from primary (Driller) panel. TIH to 14;170'. Wash; ream & drill shoe track to 14;352'. Displace mud from 12.2 ppg to 13.1 ppg SBM while drilling out shoe track.

1/4/2017- Drill cmt in 18" shoe track f/ 14;352' to 14;362'. Continue displacing mud from 12.2ppg to 13.1ppg SBM. Function test BOP's on 6.625" drill pipe from drillers control panel (primary) on blue pod; function from toolpusher control panel (secondary) on yellow pod. Function diverter on 6.625" drill pipe from toolpusher control panel (secondary). Drill shoe track & clean out rate hole to 14;506'. Drill new hole to 14;516'. R/U to perform FIT. Pressure up to 1;420 psi. with 13.1 ppg. SBM at 14;376' TVD EMW = 15.0 ppg. Surface + .26 = 15.26 ppg. Down hole EMW. Drill ahead 16.5" X 19.5" hole to 16;176'. Weight up mud from 13.3 ppg to 13.7 ppg SBM. DHMW 13.93 ppg

1/5/2017- Drilling ahead with 16.5" x 19.5" drilling assembly from 16;176' to 18;290 ' hole section TD. Weight up active mud system from 13.7 ppg to 14.1 ppg SBM. Flow check; well static. Pump 100 bbl 17.1 ppg weighted sweep and circulate bottoms up with 14.1 ppg SBM @ 18;290'. DHEMW 14.36ppg 

1/6/2017- Circ hole clean w/ 14.1 ppg SBM @ 18;290' hole section TD. Spot 40 bbls 17.0 ppg pad mud on bottom. POOH f/ 18;290' to inside csg shoe @ 14;360'. Pick up and run 16.150" csg to 1;377'.

1/7/2017-PU & RIH w/ 16.150" to 2;962'. PU & RIH w/ 16" 96.0 lb/ft csg to 3;287'. WOW for 12hrs due to vessel movement and wind.  PU & RIH w/ 16" csg to 4;805'.
"},{"   ":123,"WELL_NAME":"  003","API12":608124011300,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-01-08","TEXT_REMARK":"1/8/2016- PU & MU FMC 16" SMLH to 11;562'. RIH with 16.150"casing; 16" casing & FMC 16" SMLH on 6.625" landing string to 13;870'.

1/9/2016- RIH with 16.150" 119.23 lb/ft; HP Q-125 Seal Lock SF casing; 16"; 96 lb/ft; HP Q-125 Hyd 513 casing; FMC 16" SMLH on 6.625" landing string to 18;068. Land out 16" in SMLH at 6;632'. 117 bbls lost during circulation with 25% returns. Attempt to circ; failed. 
Break circulation and pump a total of 10 bbls of 14.8 ppg Tuned Spacer. Close the Lo-Torque and test lines to 7;000 psi. Good Test; open Lo-Torque valve. Pump 90 bbls of 14.8 ppg of Tuned Spacer III with surfactants. Drop bottom dart. Mix and Pump 1;497 sxs. Of Class H cement for 289.5 bbls ( 1;625.7 ft3.) at 16.4ppg. with a yield of 1.086 ft3/sk. Pump 10 bbls of cement and inject Protechnics Tracer at 30 MC/Hr into the next 50 bbls at the pump suction. Drop top dart. Pump 10.5 bbls of cement on top of dart. Pump 15 bbls of 14.8 ppg Tuned Spacer lll with surfactants. Displace cement with 116 bbls of 14.1 ppg SBM; land and shear top plug. Pump 10 additional bbls. Halliburton shut down pumps; continue displacing with rig pumps at 20 BPM - 3;560 psi; at 1;960 bbls slow rate to 12 BPM - 2;090 psi. At 2;218 bbls shear bottom plug with 2;976 psi. After plug shear top plug set at 2;498 bbls; pressure up to 3;500 psi (1000 psi over circulating). Shut down pumps. Pressure stabilize to 3;200 psi. Halliburton bled back 22 3/4 bbls. Check float equipment; floats holding.
Note: Shoe - 18;169'       Float Collar - 18;071.01      16" Liner Top- 6632'

Mud Lost Circulating 16" Casing: 117 bbls
Mud Lost Cementing 16" casing: 366 bbls
Mud Lost Displacing 16" Casing: 2;563 bbls
Total Mud ·Lost for 16" Casing Job: 3;046 bbls

 Attempt to set & test FMC seal assembly; failed. Observe .3 bbl per min increase in trip tank for 30 min. Decision made to POOH. POOH to 5;645'; close UBSR's. PU & TIH with mill & flush tool to 5;641'. Monitor psi below UBSR's.

1/10/2016- Continue Monitoring well w/ UBSR's closed. TIH w/ Clean out tool to 6;632'; dress off 16" profile. POOH & LD clean out tool. PU 16" BU seal assy & TIH to 6;632. Attempt to set & test seal assembly; failed. POOH & LD seal assy. TIH w/ cmt stinger to 6;832'. POOH. Position EOT @ 6;432'.  Take injection rates.
NOTE: Received verbal approval from BSEE Houma District to proceed with 16" liner squeeze job as requested; 20:02 hrs 1/10/17.

1/11/2016- Bleed off injection pressure. TIH w/ stinger to 6;632'. Cement unit pump 10 bbls 14.8 ppg tuned spacer 3. Test surface lines @ 5;000 psi (Good Test). Pump 40 bbls 14.8 ppg tuned spacer 3. Mix & pump 80 bbls (449.2 ft3) 16.4 ppg cement; 415 sks; yield - 1.082 ft3/sk at 5 bpm. Pump 5 bbls 14.8ppg tuned spacer 3. Displace spacer & cement with 175 bbls 14.1 ppg at 6 bpm to leave cement 5.7 bbls under displaced. Cement plug set from 6;632' to 6;404'. POOH to 6;254'. Squeeze 80 bbls cmt to 50' below 16" liner top @ 6;632'. Pump 85 bbls 14.1 ppg to displace cement 50' below 16" top of liner. Cement in place at 05:15 hrs. WOC; monitoring annulus pressure on choke line w/ lower annular closed; 1;620 psi to 385 psi.
Note: Received verbal approval from BSEE Houma District granting 24 hr BOP function/pressure tests extension; 14:45 hrs 01-11/17.
Note: Received verbal approval from BSEE Houma District to proceed with second squeeze if necessary once PE certification is obtained; 22:32 hrs 01-11-17.

1/12/2016- WOC. Open up & monitor well; well static. Attempt to test 16" liner top; failed. TIH to 6;623' tag cmt; wash dn to 6;671'. POOH. Funct UBSR; CSR & LBSR from drillers control panel (primary) on yellow pod. Function test BOP's with 6.625" drill pipe from drillers control panel (primary) on yellow pod. Test BOP's on 6.625" drill pipe with 14.1ppg SBM. Test from toolpusher control panel (secondary) on blue pod utilizing OTC Greenlight Test System. Test all rams and related valves to 300 psi low - 7;600 psi high; test all annulars; related valves and kelly hose to 300 psi low - 5;000 psi high. BOP tests 1 - 9 complete. TIH w/ clean out / BOP test assy to 6;413'.
NOTE: Received verbal approval from BSEE Houma District granting additional 24 hr BOP function/pressure tests extension; 01-12-17.

1/13/2016- Function CSR's from toolpusher control panel (secondary) on blue pod. Test BOP's on 6.625" drill pipe with 14.1ppg SBM. Test from toolpusher control panel (secondary) on blue pod utilizing OTC Greenlight Test System. Test upper & lower blind shear rams and related valves to 300 psi low - 7;600 psi high. Tests 13 of 13 complete. Function test Diverter from DCP. TIH w/ 14.5" Clean Out assy to 6;579'; wash dn to 6;955'. Circ BU. POOH 6;622'. Attempt to test liner top; failed. POOH to RKB. TIH w/ open ended 6.625" DP to 1;920'.

1/14/2016- TIH open ended 6.625" drill pipe to 6;832'. POOH to 6;622'. Perform injection rates w/ 14.1 ppg SBM. Perform 16" liner top squeeze # 2: Pumped 30 bbls of 14.8 ppg tuned spacer 3. Pump 30 bbls 6.7 base oil. Pump 20 bbls of 14.8 ppg tuned spacer III. Mix & pump 110 bbls (617.5 ft3) of 16.4 ppg cement; 570.7 sks; Yield = 1.082 fts/sk. Pump cement at 5 bpm. Pump 3 bbls of 14.8 ppg tuned spacer III with surfactants behind. Using Halliburton pumps continue displacing with 14.1ppg SBM; spotting 30 bbls of Tuned Spacer III in annulus. After pumping 29 bbls of 14.1ppg SBM; close Kill line and squeeze 30 bbls of base oil; 20 bbls of Tuned Spacer III and 87 bbls of cement below TOL. With 167 bbls displaced observe pressure of 2;860 psi pumping at 0.1bpm (23 bbls of cement left in pipe). Shut down. Bleed pressure at cement unit. Open kill line; and Halliburton pump additional 17 bbls displacement down drill string to balance cement. Wait on cement holding squeeze with annular closed . Monitor annulus pressure. DHEMW- 14.4ppg
"},{"   ":124,"WELL_NAME":"  003","API12":608124011300,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-01-15","TEXT_REMARK":"1/15/2017-  Continue WOC & monitoring annulus pressure. Bled off pressure. POOH to RKB. MU 18.125" clean out assy & TIH to 6;250'. Wash & ream dn w/ 14.1 ppg SBM to 6;526'; tag cmt. Drill cmt dn to 6;632' 16" TOL. Circ BU. POOH to 6;122'.


1/16/2017-POOH w/ 18.125" assy  to RKB. MU & TIH w/ 14.5" assy to 6;632'. Drill cmt to 6;685'. TIH to 7;630'. Test 16" csg @ 2;100 psi - Good test. TIH to 15;600'. Establish rates with 14.1ppg SBM & Log dn to 16;990'. NOTE: TOC behind 16" Casing = 16;863'. TIH to 17;889'. Wash dn to 18;054'; tag cmt. Test 16" csg @ 2;100 psi f/ 30 min - Good test.


1/17/2017- Drill cement & 16" shoe track with 14.5" PWD/Clean out assembly to 18;162'. Clean out rat hole to 18;290'. Drill 10' new hole to 18;300'. RU & perform 16" csg shoe FIT with 14.1ppg SBM to 1465psi (15.64 EMW/ 15.84 DHEMW). POOH w/ 14.5 PWD/clean out assy to RKB. MU & TIH w/ 14.5" X 17.5" drlg assy to 4; 115'.


1/18/2017-TIH w/ 14.5 " x 17.5" BHA to 18;106'. Function test BOP #2 against 6.625" DP on blue pod from primary (driller) panel. Swap pods. Function test BOP #2 against 6.625" on yellow pod from secondary (tool pusher) panel. Function test diverter system from secondary (tool pusher) panel. Slack off to bottom; open the reamer and drill to 19;260'. Weight up Mud system to 14.4ppg SBM. DHEMW 14.53ppg.


1/19/2017- Continue drilling ahead w/ 14.5" x 17.5" drilling assembly to 20;950'. Weight Up Mud to 14.2ppg; DHEMW 14.70ppg


1/20/2017- Continue drilling ahead w/ 14.5" x 17.5" drilling assembly to 22;660'. Weight up mud to 14.8ppg; DHEMW 15.1ppg


1/21/2017- Continue drilling ahead w/ 14.5" x 17.5" drilling assembly to 24;260'. Weight up mud to 15.1ppg; DHEMW 15.3ppg

"},{"   ":125,"WELL_NAME":"  003","API12":608124011300,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-01-22","TEXT_REMARK":"1/22/2017- Continue drilling ahead w/ 14.5" x 17.5" drilling assembly to ± 25;488'. 15.1ppg-S; 15.3ppg-DH. Weight up mud from 15.1ppg-S to 15.3ppg-S. 


1/23/2017-Continue to weight up mud from 15.1ppg-S to 15.3ppg-S; 15.55ppg-DH. POOH w/Schlumberger 14.5" x 17.5" drilling assembly. Function test BOP on 6.625'' DP from Primary panel on Yellow POD- good test. Swap Pod to Blue. Function test BOP on Blue POD on secondary panel- good test. Function diverter from Primary panel- good test.  Continue to POOH to RKB. Function Upper; Lower and casing blind shear rams from Blue POD primary panel - good test. Swap to Yellow POD and Function Upper; Lower and casing blind shear rams from Secondary panel - good test.


1/24/2017- RIH w/ 14.15" 115.53# Q125HP SLSF casing to 9;459'


1/25/2017- Continue RIH with 14" Hyd 523 casing from 9;459' to 19;318'. PU 14" FMC hanger and TIH to 20;111' with 14'' casing on 6.625'' Landing String.


1/26/2017- TIH to 25;327 with 14'' casing on 6.625'' Landing String. Land hanger at 5978' Increase flow rate to 4 bpm with 1;036 psi and pump 120 bbls with no returns. 

Cement 14" casing. Pump 100 bbls of 15.8 ppg Tuned spacer. Drop bottom dart; mix and pump 433 bbls; 2;239 sks of 16.4 ppg Class H cement (2;431.6 ft3; 1.086 ft3/sk yield). Drop the top dart and pump 7.4 bbls of cement followed by 15 bbls of 15.8 ppg of tuned spacer with surfactants. Displace with 77 bbls of 15.3 ppg SBM and latch the top dart into the top plug; note shear out at 3500 psi. Turn over displacement to the rig. Pump at 840 gpm 4;000 psi for 2;407 bbls pumped; slow pumps to 420 gpm with 2;070 psi. Noted bottom plug land @ 2;543 bbls pumped and shear out with 2;808 psi. Stage pumps back up to 630 gpm with 3360 psi to 2;850 bbls pumped. Slow pumps down to 420 gpm with 2900 psi and land out top plug @ 2;995 bbls pumped. Shut down pumps with 3900 psi on drill string. Halliburton bled off drill string and floats held. Note CMT in place @ 16:01 hrs. No returns during CMT Job. Total losses for CMT Job = 3;084 bbls of 15.3 ppg S.B.M. Set 14'' seal assy. Close middle pipe rams primary station yellow POD and apply 9000 psi to energize seal assy. Bled off pressure. Test seal assy to 7200 psi POOH with Landing string

Estimated TOC = 21700' determined by lift pressure. RA tracers included in cement will run Gamma ray log in real time to determine actual TOC.
Top of casing @ 5;977.07'
Float Collar @ 25;262.20'
Shoe @ 25;348.00'



1/27/2017- TIH w/ 12.25" X 14.25" BHA assembly and land out same in the wellhead. Locate upper annular with 5" drill pipe and function test BOP's from Tool pusher panel (Secondary) on blue pod. Test BOP's with 15.3 ppg SBM on 5" drill pipe from Rig floor panel (Primary) on yellow pod. Test annulars; kelly hose; and all related valves to 300 psi low/ 5;000 psi high - good test. Test rams and all related valves to 300 psi low/ 8;500 psi high - good test. Function test casing shear rams on Yellow POD from primary (Rig floor Panel) - good test. Pressure Test Upper and Lower BSR's with 15.3 ppg S.B.M. to 250 psi low / 8;500 psi high on Yellow POD from primary (Drill floor Panel) - good test. Swap to Blue POD and function test upper; lower and casing blind shear rams from Blue POD secondary panel. (Tool pushers panel) - good test. Function Diverter on 6.625'' pipe from Secondary panel - good test. POOH. Close fail safe valve and pressure test surface lines to 7500 psi - good test. Open fail safe valve and close lower blind shear rams primary panel Blue POD and begin pressure testing 14'' casing to 7;100 psi.


1/28/2017- Continue testing 14" casing to 7;100 psi for 30 mins - good test. TIH w/ 12.25" X 14.25" BHA on 6 5/8" drill pipe to 18;224'.
"},{"   ":126,"WELL_NAME":"  003","API12":608124011300,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-01-29","TEXT_REMARK":"1/29/2017- Log with the ARC to locate TOC on the backside to 22;520'. Actual TOC on backside of 14" casing = 22;260'. TIH w/ 6.625" DP to 25;115'. Displace mud system from 15.3 ppg SBM to 14.8 ppg BaraECD SBM. Drill cement and shoe track. Drilling firm cmt from 25;265' to 14'' shoe @ 25;348'. Drill 10' of new formation with 12.25'' X 14.25'' drilling assy from 25;488' to 25;498'. Circulate and POOH to 25;240'. DHEMW = 15.1ppg


1/30/2017- Perform FIT to 2;060psi surface pressure with 14.8 ppg SBM at 25;348'

"},{"   ":140,"WELL_NAME":"  003a","API12":608124010100,"WAR_START_DT":"2015-05-25","TEXT_REMARK":"First report of operations for drilling.

5/26/15 -

5/28/15 -

5/29/2015 -

5/30/2015 -

6/2/2015 -

Land BOP's @ 01:05hrs on WR51 #3. Perform ROV Intervention and test t/ 1;000 psi for 5 min. Deadman / Auto Shear. Test upper BSR and 22" casing to 250/4;300 psi for 30 min. TIH w/ test assembly. Test on 6.625'' Drill pipe with sea water.

6/5/2015 -

CBU f/ 25;000' displace 15.0 ppg SBM to 14.9 ppg SBM. Cont TIH w/ 8.5" Clean-Out Assy. f/ 25;000' to 28;948'. MU TDX; cir BU f/28;948' displace 15.0 ppg SBM to 14.9 ppg SBM. TIH f/ 28;930' to 30;063'. Wash/Ream down f/30;138' to 30;449'.

7/14/16 -
W/R f/ 30;449' to 31;022' bit depth; Reamer depth - 30;972'. Open new hole f/31;022' to 31;081' bit depth. (30;972' to 31;032' reamer depth.)CBU to TOL and Pump out of hole to TOL. CBU to surface. POOH

7/15/16 -
POOH from 24;621' to 23;464'. Pump 90 bbls of slug and chase with 20 bbls of 14.9 ppg SBM. Function test BOP's and Diverter from the TP panel; blue pod. Function Upper; lower and casing shear rams from blue pod TP panel. POOH & Rack back 8.5'' Clean out BHA. RIH with MDT tool string from 300' to 28;000'.

7/16/16 -
RIH with MDT-Pressure tool string f/ 28;000' to 30;177'. POOH; unable to get past 30;177'. PU Run #4 & RIH to 30;177'. POOH; unable to get past. Rig down same. Pick up 8.5" OnTrak BHA assy."},{"   ":196,"WELL_NAME":"  004","API12":608124010900,"WAR_START_DT":"2016-07-17","TEXT_REMARK":"7/17/2016 - TIH with OnTrax/TesTrak assembly to 24;142'; CBU every 5;000'. 

7/18/2016 - Continue TIH to 30;155'; CBU every 5;000'.  Washed/reamed to 30;165'. Log up f/ 30;875' to 30;765'. Attempted to take formation samples - unsuccessful.  Pumped out to 30;168'. Washed/Reamed to bottom and pumped out of hole to 30;942.

7/19/2016 - Continued pump out of the hole at reduced rate to 25;032'. CBU at 25;032' with 14.9 ppg; max gas 945 units; mud cut to 14.7 ppg.  Pumped slug and POOH to 12;456'.  Funct BOPs from DCP; Blue Pod. Pressure tested BOPs from TCP; Yellow Pod on 4-1/2" DP with 14.9 ppg SBM; annulars to 250 psi low / 5;000 psi high; rams to 250 psi low / 9;500 psi high.

7/20/2016 - Continued pressure testing BOPs on 4-1/2" and 6-5/8" DP from TCP; Yellow pod with 14.9 ppg SBM; annulars to 250 psi low / 5;000 high; rams to 250 psi low / 9;500 psi high.  TIH with cleanout assembly.  Functioned diverter.  Pressure tested BSRs to 9;500 psi.  Function tested BSRs and CSRs from DCP; Yellow pod.  POOH with cleanout/test assembly.

7/21/2016 - POOH from 17;146' to 12;840'.  Remove test assembly.  TIH with 8-1/2" x 9-7/8" clean out assy to 15;000'.  CBU to above WH with 14.9ppg SBM.  TIH to 20;000'. CBU to above WH with 14.9 ppg SBM.  TIH to 25;000'.  CBU to above WH with 14.9 ppg SBM.

NOTE:  Received 72-hr extension for 30-day casing evaluation from BSEE Mr. Bobby Nelson.

7/22/2016 - CBU to WH at 25;000'.  TIH with 8-1/2" X 9-7/8" clean out assy to 29;834'. CBU to TOL.  TIH to 30;166'.  Reamed tar section as required.  Pumped and reamed out of hole to 25;032'.  CBU with 14.9 ppg SBM.

7/23/2016 - Well static. POOH wet with cleanout assembly to 23;747'.  Pumped slug.  Continued POOH.  Functioned BSRs and CSR from DCP; Yellow Pod.  PU and RIH with logging assembly."},{"   ":197,"WELL_NAME":"  004","API12":608124010900,"WAR_START_DT":"2016-07-24","TEXT_REMARK":"7/24/2016- TIH w/ SLB MDT / TLC tools to 29;920'. RU side entry sub. RIH w/ SLB Wet Connect tool to 29;772'. Attempt to latch WC tool w/ no success.

7/25/2016- SLB wireline POOH to 10;000' Pump & displace 150 bbls low LCM concentration mud. SLB RIH & latch Wet Connect Tool. Take MDT pressure samples as per Anadarko Wireline Log program . Suspend logging program due to Node 5 failure on BOP system. POOH w/ SLB Wet Connect tool to 6;000'

7/26/2016- SLB POOH w/ Wet Connect tool to 600'. Break out side entry sub & pull Wet Connect to RKB. POOH w/ SLB MDT/TLC assy f/ 29;920' to 1;142'. Perform Negative test on LBSR; Good Test. Power down BOP Node 5 & make required repairs. POOH to 168' & LD SLB tools.

NOTE:  Received verbal approval for 7 day casing evaluation extension due to pending TA operations from Bobby Nelson on 7/26/16.

7/27/2016- Repair BOP Node 5 & commission Node 5. Change out SLB wireline spool. TIH w/ MDT/TLC assy to 5;423'. Receive BSEE RPD approval f/ Node 5 repair. TIH w/ MDT/TLC assy to 12;500'. Function UBSR's; CSR's & LBSR's from Toolpusher Control Panel on Yellow Pod. Funct Test BOP's from Drillers Control Panel on Yellow Pod; from Toolpusher Control Panel on Blue Pod. Function Diverter from Toolpusher Control Panel. TIH w/ MDT/TLC to 15;226'.

7/28/2016- TIH w/ MDT/TLC assy to 20;017'. Slip & cut drill line;  function test crown saver. Circ 14.9 ppg SBM. TIH to 25;156'. Circ @ TOL. TIH to 29;913'. Circ 1 tubing volumes. RU SLB side entry sub & RIH w/ Wet Connect tool & latch same. TIH to 30;652'. Log well.

7/29/2016- Performing MDT pressure samples as per Anadarko Wireline Logging Program Run # 2; 20 pressures and 6 samples taken. Run # 2 total; 24 pressures & 7 samples taken.

7/30/2016- POOH w/ SLB MDT assy f/ 30;201' to 29;913'. Remove clamp f/ side entry sub. Activate Wet Connect disconnect. POOH w/ Wet Connect to 200'. Break out side entry sub; pull out w/ Wet Connect tool & LD same. POOH w/ MDT/TLC assy from 29;913' to 1;135'."},{"   ":198,"WELL_NAME":"  004","API12":608124010900,"WAR_START_DT":"2016-07-31","TEXT_REMARK":"7/31/2016- POOH w/ MDT/TLC assy f/ 1;135' to 162'. LD MDT tools & recover sample product. RIH w/ 3.5" sacrificial tbg & BHKA assy to 30;047'. Break circ & wash down to 30;285'. String taking wt; work string dn to 30;345'. 271.1 bbls mud lost

8/1/2016- Work & wash tubing/BHKA assy down f/ 30;345' to 30;357' w/ partial to no mud returns. Pump out of hole to 24;826' above TOL. Circ BU @ 24;826' w/ 14.9 ppg SBM. Flow check well; well static. Pump slug & POOH w/ tubing/BHKA assy to 21;098'. 184 bbls mud lost.

NOTE:  On 8/1/16 Bobby Nelson approval granted for additional 7 day casing evaluation extension or as soon as possible once open hole is isolated

8/2/2016- POOH w/ sacrificial tubing/BHKA assy to 16;600'. Service traveling equip & perform full block calibration. POOH w/ tubing/BHKA assy. PU 7" bit; +/- 900' 4.5" DP & BHKA. TIH & test BOP's on 4.5" & 6.625" DP with 14.9 ppg SBM to 250 psi low and 9500 psi high from toolpusher panel on yellow pod.  Test annulars to 250 psi low and 5;000 psi high.

NOTE:  BSEE Inspectors arrived onboard at 09:02 hrs. and departed at 15:00 hrs. 0 INCs.

8/3/2016- Finish testing BOP's. Function test diverter from rig floor. TIH to the 10 1/8" shoe. Break circulation and begin wash/ream from 30;082' to 30;155'. 206 bbls mud lost.

8/4/2016- Finish washing and reaming from 30;155' to 31;100'. Perform cement job.  Mix and pump 373 cu.ft. of 16.0 ppg Class H cement.  Cement in place at 07:26 hrs. Rack back cement head and Pump out of hole to 25;817'. 1;240 bbls mud lost.

8/5/2016- Pump out of the hole with BHKA f/ 25;817' to 24;919'. POOH w/ 10 stand wet to 23;762'. Pump 90 bbls of 18.0 ppg slug & chase same w/ 20bbls of 14.9 ppg SBM. POOH to surface. TIH From RKB to 16;663' with 8.5" rock bit and 8.625" casing scraper.  258 bbls mud lost.

8/6/2016- Continue TIH f/ 16;663' to 27;500'. W/R w/8.625" scraper assy F/27;500' to 30;115'. Pump out to 25;140'; no drag noted. TIH to 28;100'. 603 bbls mud lost."},{"   ":199,"WELL_NAME":"  004","API12":608124010900,"WAR_START_DT":"2016-08-07","TEXT_REMARK":"8/7/2016- TIH w/ scraper assy to 30;112'. Pump out of hole 25;156'; cir @ 25;156'. Spot 490 bbls of 16.5 ppg SBM in riser @ displace w/ 200 bbls to surface. Pump 100 bbl slug. POOH f/ 25;156' to 17;695'.

8/8/2016- POOH f/ 17;695' to 5;633'. Boost riser Displace 163 bbl 16.5 ppg SBM riser cap with 14.9 ppg SBM. POOH w/ 8.625" scraper assy on 4.5" DP. Run in the hole with Schlumberger E-line IBC-MSIP Run #1 to 25;156' log f/ 30;082' to 21;775'.

NOTE:  Justin Ledet granted verbal approval on 8/8/16 for an additional 48 hrs. for casing pressure test due to increased trip time.

8/9/2016- Cont to log up w/ SLB e-line #1 POOH to surface. RIH w/ run #2 & set packer @ 29;984'. POOH to surface. R/D wireline eq. P/U Hall/MST and TIH. Test 14"x10 1/8" csg. to 2888 psi with 14.9 ppg SBM for 30 mins. BSEE test. Function CSR;LBSR and UBSR from DCP Blue Pod. Function UBSR; CSR and LBSR from TCP Yellow Pod.

8/10/2016- TIH w/ Halliburton MST assy f/ 16;180' to 19;135'. Performed Function Test from DCP Yellow Pod and TCP Blue Pod. Performed Diverter function test; 35 seconds to
close. TIH to 29;976'. Sting back into EZSVB w/ 30k down. Pump 14.9 ppg SBM; squeezing 35 bbls of tuned spacer III and 80 bbls of 16.0ppg Class H cement below EZSVB with 80K down. Cement in place @ 10:45 hrs. Reverse out. rig down cmt lines. POOH to 24;921'. M/U TDX pump 100 bbl slug @ chase same w/ 20 bbls of 14.9 ppg.

8/11/2016- POOH w/ 6.625" DP & stinger assembly to 5;040'. Change handling equipment to 4.5". POOH w/ 4.5" DP & stinger assy f/ 5;040' to surface. TIH w/ 4.5" DP open ended to 25;300' Set FMC insert bushing at 5;921. Perform negative test by displacing drill string with 178 bbls of SW. Shut down and noted 2;762 psi differential. Close lower annular and test rams; apply 700 psi between same Bled back differential pressure to 0 psi and monitor for no flow.

8/12/2016- Finish the negative test. Pump down the CST to 25;310'. Pump cmt plug #3 from 24;800' to 25;300'; 355 cu.ft of 17.0 ppg Class H cement. P/U and pump a foam ball. Displace the well from 24;800' to 6800' with 588 bbls. of 16.5 SBM. POOH to surface

8/13/2016- TIH w/14" FasDril & riser brushes to 6;456'. Set packer. Weighted test packer with 25k down. Disp well f/ 6;456' to surface w/ 8.6 ppg seawater. Mix; pump cement for top plug - 125.31 cu.ft of 16.4 ppg Class H cement. Cement in place @ 14:17 hrs. Top of plug from 6;456' to 6;306' (150' plug). R/B Cmt head. POOH to 6;205'. Pump riser flush. Spot 57 bbls of MEG f/ 6;205' to 5;917'. POOH

NOTE:  Received verbal approval from Justin Ledet on 8/13/16 to revise the surface plug setting depth and volume."},{"   ":200,"WELL_NAME":"  004","API12":608124010900,"WAR_START_DT":"2016-08-14","TEXT_REMARK":"8/14/2016- POOH w/ riser brushes to surface. R/U riser tools. Remove diverter P/U landing joint and lock slip jt. Unlatch the BOP and move the rig 500' to safe zone. L/D riser to jnt.#35 (2;677).  Performed 600' radius; site clearance; bottom scan survey.  Removed 1 plastic bottle from seafloor at 182' from well.  No other debris observed.

8/15/2016- Pull marine riser. Remove bulls eyes & clamps f/ LMRP. R/D riser running equipment & spider. Skid Stack to park position. Matched LMRP1 to BOP1 and LMRP2 to BOP2.  

8/16/2016- Finish Cleaning mud pits and shaker area. Laying down drill pipe.

8/17/2016- FMC T/A cap installed on wellhead."}]
